---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const essays = await getCollection('essays');
essays.sort((a, b) => (a.data.order ?? 99) - (b.data.order ?? 99));

const fmt = (d: Date) =>
  d.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'short', day: 'numeric' });

const isRecent = (d?: Date) => {
  if (!d) return false;
  const days = (Date.now() - d.getTime()) / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24);
  return days < 21;
};
---
<Base title="parrik" description="On love — distributed systems, biology, the practice.">
  <section class="intro">
    <h1>on love</h1>
    <p>Love here isn't enthusiasm. It's the willingness to stay with something long enough that it starts to show you its structure.</p>
    <p>Stay long enough and the structure starts to repeat. Shuffle sharding and cellular architecture are the same answer in different vocabularies. A fractal is itself a distributed shape. A cell that has lost its tissue's broadcast is shaped the way a node losing quorum is shaped.</p>
    <p>What gets studied here — across distributed systems, biology, the practice — is what happens when a living thing stops knowing it's part of something larger.</p>
    <p>Posters, short pieces, longer prose. Written by AI, lived by human.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="essays">
    <h2>Essays</h2>
    <ul>
      {essays.map((essay) => {
        const d = essay.data;
        const showTended = d.updatedAt && d.publishedAt && isRecent(d.updatedAt) &&
          (d.updatedAt.getTime() - d.publishedAt.getTime() > 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
        return (
          <li>
            <a href={`/essays/${essay.id}/`} class="essay-link">
              <div class="essay-head">
                <span class="essay-title">{d.title}</span>
                <span class="essay-dateline">
                  {d.tag && <span class="dl-tag">{d.tag}</span>}
                  {d.status && <span class="dl-sep">·</span>}
                  {d.status && <span class={`dl-status dl-status-${d.status}`}>{d.status}</span>}
                  {showTended && <span class="dl-sep">·</span>}
                  {showTended && <span class="dl-tended">tended {fmt(d.updatedAt!)}</span>}
                </span>
              </div>
              {d.subtitle && <p class="essay-subtitle">{d.subtitle}</p>}
            </a>
          </li>
        );
      })}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="currently">
    <h2>Currently</h2>
    <p>Writing the next essay. Reading DDIA Chapter&nbsp;9. Practicing the piano. The next post is about the shape itself — why signal-responsive-system is a frame worth naming rather than three coincidences.</p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .intro { margin: 0.5rem 0 2.5rem; }
  .intro h1 {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1.9rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .intro p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
    max-width: 34rem;
  }
  .intro p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .essays,
  .currently {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .essays h2,
  .currently h2 {
    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .essays ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .essays li {
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }
  .essays li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .essay-link {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text);
    display: block;
  }

  .essay-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .essay-title {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.003em;
  }

  .essay-link:hover .essay-title {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .essay-dateline {
    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-variant: tabular-nums;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .essay-dateline .dl-tag {
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }
  .essay-dateline .dl-sep {
    margin: 0 0.4em;
    color: var(--line);
  }
  .essay-dateline .dl-status,
  .essay-dateline .dl-tended {
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .essay-dateline .dl-status-tending {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .essay-subtitle {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  .currently p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 38rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .intro h1 { font-size: 1.7rem; }
    .intro p { font-size: 1rem; }
    .essay-head { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.25rem; }
    .essay-dateline { white-space: normal; }
  }
</style>
